		<!-- message -->
		<div>i look at it this way:<br />
<br />
IGE, et al, do not drive the market for money bought items. they didn't just up and one day go 'ya know, we're going to spontaneously create a market enviornment for ourselves.'<br />
items and plat and accounts being sold for cash is a totally player driven thing, done because players want it to be done. if you got rid of IGE, if every ebay type site was shut down, if EVERY public avenue was removed, you would still have people contacting each other in game, over private message boards, or any number of ways, to sell things.<br />
<br />
so, here's the situation:<br />
the problem on normal servers is that the players on that server will buy plat, items, and accounts... and thereby get shit they didn't earn. <br />
the point of the Exchange servers isn't to try to siphon off IGE or what have you... it's to try and siphon off the players who would be inclined to do that sort of thing. get them in all in one place: let them fuck up their own server as much as they want... it's that many fewer people on the real servers screwing things up for everyone else</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
